  "prompt": "How do you factory reset an iPhone 4 without a computer?",
  "response": "To factory reset an iPhone 4 without a computer, follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to \"Settings\" on your iPhone 4\n\n2. Tap \"General\"\n\n3. Scroll down and tap \"Reset\"\n\n4. Select \"Erase All Content and Settings\"\n\n5. Enter your passcode if prompted\n\n6. Confirm that you want to erase the device\n\nThe iPhone will then reset to its original factory settings. Note that this will delete all data on the phone, so make sure you've backed up any important information beforehand.\n\nIf you cannot access the Settings menu, you can also try:\n- Restoring through Recovery Mode (which typically requires a computer)\n- Using iTunes on a computer if possible\n\nFor the most modern and reliable reset method, having a computer is recommended.",
